      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De temperantia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e112">Is qui praeest, ea se circa subditos mensura
              moderetur, quatenus et arridens timeri debeat, et iratus amari: ut eum nec nimia
              laetitia vilem reddat, nec immoderata severitas odiosum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e127">Nonnunquam, dum nonnulla menti delectatio
              surrepit, temperantia nostra marcescit. In quantum enim ad delectationem ducimur, in
              tantum minus ab illicitis temperamus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in
              <title>Homiliis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e142">In talibus mentibus Dominus pascitur, quae per
              respectum gratiae temperatae corporalibus desideriis non utuntur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e157">Romanorum semper ab antiquioribus usus fuit,
              post admixtionem propriae conjugis lavari et purificationem quaerere, et ab ingressu
              ecclesiae paululum reverenter abstinere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in
              <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e173">Quoties ira animum invadit, mentem edoma, vince
              teipsum, differ tempus furoris; cum tranquilla mens fuerit, quod placet
              vindica.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in
              <title>Pastorali</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e188">Cum non malitia, sed sola ignorantia, vel
              infirmitate delinquitur, profecto necesse est ut magno moderamine ipsa delicti
              correptio temperetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e195">Augustinus,
              <title>de Libero –êrbitrio</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e203">Temperantia est afflictio coercens et cohibens
              appetitum ab his rebus, quae turpiter appetuntur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e210">Augustinus,
              <title>de Confessionibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e218" source="http://scta.info/resource/aconf-l10-d1e339">
              De illecebra odorum non satago nimis: cum
              absunt, non requiro: cum adsunt, non respuo: semper tamen carere paratus.
            </quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e225">Augustinus,
              <title>de Opere Monachorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e233">Tanto gloriosius mens ad superiora promovetur,
              quanto diligentius ab inferioribus concupiscentia cohibetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e240">Augustinus,
              <title>de Singularitate Clericorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e248">Disce nunc temperantiae modum, qui per licentiam
              quaeris excessum. Ama feminas inter sacra solemnia, et odio habe in communione
              privata.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e256">Augustinus,
              <title>de Moribus Ecclesiae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e264">Omne officium temperantiae est exuere veterem
              hominem, et in Deo renovari, id est contemnere omnes corporeas illecebras laudemque
              popularem, totumque amorem ad invisibilia et divina conferre.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e271">Augustinus,
              <title>de Moribus Ecclesiae</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e279">Curiosi esse prohibemur, quod magnae
              temperantiae munus est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e286">Isidorus,
              <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e294">Quidquid nimis et ultra modum est, perniciosum
              fit, studiumque suum in contrarium vertit. In omni ergo opere modum et temperamentum
              oportet habere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e301">Isidorus, in
              <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e309">In omni re tene temperamentum. Nihil
              intemperantius agas, nec minus, nec nimium aliquid, nec ultra quam oportet, nec infra.
              Etiam in bonis moderatum esse decet.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e316">Isidorus, in
              <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e324">Quae cum temperantia fiunt, salubria sunt, et
              bona quaevis etiam, cum immoderato usu, noxia efficiuntur. Nimietas enim omnis in
              vitio deputatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e339" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e331">Bernardus,
              <title>de Consideratione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e339">Non est temperantia in solis resecandis
              superfluis; est etiam in admittendis necessariis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-d1e345">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e355" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Rd1e347">Tullius, in
              <title>Rhetoricis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e23317-Qd1e355">Temperantia est rationis in libidinem, atque in
              alios non rectos impetus animi firma et moderata dominatio: ejus partes, continentia,
              clementia, modestia.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
